      <h2>About Georgia</h2>
      <p><b>Georgia</b> is a country located in the Caucasus region of Eurasia, at the crossroads of Eastern Europe and Western Asia. It is bordered by the Black Sea in the west, Turkey and Armenia in the south, and Azerbaijan in the southeast. The capital and largest city is Tbilisi.</p>
      <p>Georgia is a member of the United Nations, Council of Europe, and GUAM Organization for Democracy and Economic Development. As of 2017, Georgia was ranked 13th in the Index of Economic Freedom and 16th in the Ease of Doing Business rankings. Georgia is also known for being a foreigner-friendly country with a very low crime rate.</p>
    </section>

<section>
    <h2>Education in Georgia</h2>
    <p>Higher education in Georgia is segregated into three categories:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Bachelor Program</li>
        <li>Master’s Program</li>
        <li>Doctorate Program</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Georgia’s education system follows the European Bologna Process and is recognized by the European Union. According to UNICEF, Georgia has made major progress in education, consistently showing good student outcomes and maintaining a transparent, corruption-free education system.</p>
    <p>Medical universities in Georgia are authorized by the government and accredited by the <b>National Center for Educational Quality Enhancement</b> . Medical studies start with a <b> 6-year / 360 credit</b>  Certified Medical Doctor (MD) program.</p>
    <p>Post-course opportunities:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Work as Junior Doctors</li>
        <li>Conduct research or teach</li>
        <li>Join residency programs and take certification exams in Georgia or countries like India (via MCI/FMGE)</li>
        <li>Pursue higher studies (Doctorate)</li>
    </ul>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>🌍 Global Career Pathways After Graduation for MBBS students ( Faculty of medicine )</h2>
    <p>Medical graduates from Georgia are eligible to pursue<b> residency and licensing </b> in several top countries, after qualifying the required medical licensing exams:</p>
    <ul>
        <li class="flag">🇮🇳 India: Pass FMGE/NExT for residency and practice.</li>
        <li class="flag">🇬🇧 UK: Pass PLAB 1 & 2, register with GMC, and start residency.</li>
        <li class="flag">🇺🇸 USA: Pass USMLE Steps 1–3, apply for NRMP Match, join residency.</li>
        <li class="flag">🇦🇺 Australia: Pass AMC exams, join internship/residency.</li>
        <li class="flag">🇨🇦 Canada: Pass MCCQE, join CaRMS for residency.</li>
        <li class="flag">🇩🇪 Germany: Apply for Approbation, join tuition-free salaried residency.</li>
    </ul>
</section>

